FT  23 JUN 93 / Welsh investment projects backed
SIX INDUSTRIAL projects in Wales, involving more than Pounds 12m of
investment and expected to create 240 jobs, were announced yesterday. The
projects are backed by Pounds 3.7m of regional selective assistance from the
Welsh Office.
The biggest project is a Pounds 6.5m expansion of production facilities by
Solvay Automotive at Treforest, Mid Glamorgan. About 130 jobs are expected
to be created at the plant, which makes plastic parts for the motor
industry.
